The paper deals with the Independent Set problem on special graph classes, which is a classic topic in theoretical computer science and falls under the category of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also involves the study of parameterized complexity and fixed-parameter algorithms, which are common in computational complexity theory (cs.CC). The use of interval graphs and their structural properties suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the field of graph theory (cs.GT). Additionally, the paper involves experiments with random data, which could indicate a focus on machine learning or data mining (cs.DM) or statistical learning (cs.LG).
